cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about temporal information extraction from text, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new models and training methods, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper involves predicting start and end-points for events, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses TimeML-style annotations, which is a format for representing temporal information, and this is related to neural networks (cs.NE) which are commonly used in NLP and CL.
